<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=OT&message.id=8298#M8298">1</a> of 26
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 337 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		
				background-color: #050A0E; 
				
				 background-image: none;
				 
				background-repeat: repeat-x;
				" 
			>
			<DIV>Well, I just got back from being "deferred" from Jury service and I am a bit heated.&nbsp; Yes, this is a rant!&nbsp; I own a business and have no employees so&nbsp;I asked for excusal&nbsp;based on a hardship.&nbsp; If I'm not open, I make no money.&nbsp;&nbsp;Two weeks of being closed&nbsp;would kill me. &nbsp;With the current state of the economy in our town, I'm lucky&nbsp;I make any money at the moment.&nbsp; So the judge gets to the point of telling who gets excused or deferred and when he gets to me says that I am deferred, but make sure I have someone to take care of my business next time.&nbsp; Umm, excuse me??&nbsp; So you're telling me I have to hire someone to take care of my store for who knows how long, when I can't afford to&nbsp;pay them!&nbsp;&nbsp; That doesn't seem right to me.&nbsp; You know, if I were sitting on my ass at home&nbsp;I would have no qualms about jury service.&nbsp; It probably wouldn't bother me if I were working for someone else either.&nbsp;&nbsp; But why should I&nbsp;have to hire someone or risk losing my business??&nbsp; &nbsp;Sorry to rant but I am pretty annoyed at the moment.&nbsp;&nbsp; </DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							**************************************************************************<br>Gypsy Gold does not clink and glitter, it gleams in the sun, and neighs in the dark.
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
