			If you have to go, make sure you <FONT color=#ff0066><STRONG>loudly</STRONG></FONT> voice your thoughts. Believe me, the lawyers on the two sides won't risk the chance that a very unhappy juror will mess things up for them. Don't make things up, just be brutally frank about how unhappy you are and you will find yourself excused by one lawyer or the other even though the judge is reluctant to let you go.
