		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Easiest way that I've found is to tell them that if any law officers are going to testify that you would have reservations as to whether they were telling the truth or not. I got out of one case where they were trying a guy for posession of 1 pound of pot. They asked me if I had any problems convicting someone for that charge and I told them that it didnt matter how much he had, I wouldnt do it because I thought that pot should be legalized. The judge told me that with the way the law reads, would I have a problem convicting him based on the law, I told him I thought the law was stupid and it should be legalized. They let me go right away.
<DIV></DIV>	
