		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>I have jury duty starting this Wednesday.&nbsp; I believe that voting and jury duty are small prices to pay for democracy.&nbsp; I am still a temporary employee, and if I serve I don't get paid either.&nbsp; In fact, I had a 3 week job assignment scheduled and so I deferred my jury duty to start after it ended.&nbsp; As it happened, the 3 week assignment was cancelled on me the day before it began and I got very few assignments during those three weeks.</P>
<P>But anyway.&nbsp; This is my 4th or 5th call for jury duty (I am 43).&nbsp; I have only been actually selected for a jury once and became violently ill (my gall bladder went) 2/3rds through the trial.&nbsp; Good thing they have alternates as after spending an hour violently retching in the juror bathroom I was excused.</P>
<P>In my state it is very hard to be excused from jury duty, it used to be much MUCH easier.&nbsp; However, if the doors of the business will indeed close down without you, you can be excused.&nbsp; That it will cause financial hardships to me might get me off a long-term trial but probably not a short-term.&nbsp; One nice thing is that I am excused from work search and other unemployment insurance problems.&nbsp; LOL, and yes, the state will deduct the $10 a day I get for jury duty from my UI claim.</P>
<DIV></DIV>	
