		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>My mom was called for jury duty once, and was extremely busy.&nbsp; She was going to school full time, working full time, and raising 3 young kids (she was insane and it nearly killed her til she quit school and slept for a week).&nbsp; But anyway, she had no time for jury duty.&nbsp; So they were asking questions and the lawer asked if my mom had any prejudice towards african americans.&nbsp; My mom acts all shocked and says "Why no!&nbsp; I'm not prejudiced.&nbsp; Why, I even have a black friend" (hard to express it in the written word, but it was said in a way that would make people not inclined to believe her).&nbsp; She was excused from the jury with no further comment.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I have served on a jury before.&nbsp; It was kindof a difficult case.&nbsp; It was a date rape case of sorts, a he said she said type of thing.&nbsp; It would most likely ended in an aquital, but she called him up afterwards, with the police recording the conversation.&nbsp; He was apologizing and stuff.&nbsp; She said, for instance, "why did you rape me", his response was "I don't know why, i'm sorry".&nbsp; That was enough for the jury.&nbsp; They were both quite drunk.&nbsp; Sort of a sad story as it is unlikely he would have done anything like that if he wouldn't have been so drunk, but you pay the consiquences for your actions whether you are sober or not.</DIV><p>Message Edited by Aegnor_Cuthalion on <span class=date_text>05-03-2004</span> <span class=time_text>08:33 PM</span>
