			>
			<DIV>Actually that's one nice thing about being in the Navy.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Actually I'm not sure if we have to serve or not, but... like many single sailors my legal residence is with my parents because the job can take me anywhere in the world.&nbsp; (especially when I go to a ship)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So... when I received the letter requesting that I serve on a jury, I was exempted--and even removed from the list--because I'm stationed almost 500 miles away from "home".</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<font size=1 color=ff00ff>...So desolate were those places and so deep the horror that lay on them that some of the host were unmanned, and they could neither walk nor ride further north.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Aragorn looked at them, and there was pity in his eyes rather than wrath....<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;'Go!' said Aragorn.  'But keep what honour you may, and do not run!  And there is a task which you may attempt and so be not wholly shamed.  Take your way south-west til you come to Cair Andros, and if that is still held by enemies, as I think, then re-take it, if you can; and hold it to the last in defense of Gondor and Rohan!'<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Then some being shamed by his mercy overcame their fear and went on, and the others took new hope, hearing of a manful deed within their measure that they could turn to, and they departed....
