		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>I would have no problem in doing Jury duty since my company will cover my pay while I'm gone.&nbsp; However, I have never yet been actually on the jury.&nbsp;&nbsp; My physical appearance is against me though.&nbsp; I have long hair and a full beard.&nbsp; The one time I was so far as to be called before the Judge for selection I could see the prosecutor writing furiously as I stepped forward.&nbsp; I knew at that point I was not going to serve.&nbsp; They also asked me what I thought of the drug laws and I told them that the prohibition causes more problems than it solves.&nbsp; I was under oath so to speak and required to tell the truth.&nbsp; I was excused immediately after that.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>I do suspect that the Judges are so used to people trying to wriggle out of being called that they are somewhat jaded and don't always recognize legitimate excuses when they see them.</P>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							I'm NOT lost, I'm exploring!
