<P>I do however thing that the jury of peers is important.&nbsp; To that stance, I say do this.&nbsp;&nbsp; Change the system so that the jury is an elective chance.&nbsp; People who are unemployed (alot right now), retired, etc can do it.&nbsp; As a&nbsp; matter of fact if you want your UI check for not working or your Social security, you should be required to do it in my opinion.&nbsp; Same with government disability or veterans benefits.&nbsp;&nbsp; If I were unemployed (and have been in the past) I would have seen this as serving my country and its people.&nbsp;&nbsp; Honestly don't screw with the lives of people who are out making the economy run and paying the taxes for so many of these programs, at least in my view.</P>
