		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Lawyers have spent large amounts of time doing statistical analysis of jury members that they use for jury selection.  They actually teach these results to them in law school.  For various types of trials, there are different desired and undesired jury members.  Education can play a very important role in this process.  For example, someone who is well educated will not accept as many excuses for something.  I.e. the recent trail of the ex-NBA star who shot someone on their property.  From what I read, the evidence showed that the defendant was pointing the shotgun at him, and that it went off right after loading it.  An educated person would be more likely to say, "Duh, you wave a loaded gun at someone and try to plead innocent when it goes off."  A person with a High School education might be more likely to accept it as an accident.  Like all statistics, this doesn't apply to everyone, but getting an additional 10% chance of a not guilty verdict is worth trying to get rid of the educated people on the jury.<br><br>Race and ethnicity also effects things.  During racially charged trials, that's definitely true.  The statistics show, though, that when trying to sue for lots of money due to product defects, negligence, etc. that Italians are a good jury selection.  They tend to have an attitude of, "Look what happened.  Just give him some money and that'll help things out."<br><br>Creighton Law School does mock trials to help its students get the feel for how things run.  My senior year of High School I served as one of the jurists.  They went through a selection process and afterwards said who they would have dismissed and why.  Education, and ethnicity were two of the things they mentioned that are big signals to lawyers that aren't directly related to the trial, but have a large effect statistically.	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>05-05-2004</span> <span class=time_text>03:41 PM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_rating_cell" valign=bottom nowrap 
			
			>
			
				&nbsp;
				
				<br><br><a href="javascript:lipopup('/eq/notification?board.id=OT&message.id=8829&notification.type=1', 'notification', 600, 460, 'yes', 'yes')" class=text_smallest><u>Report Abuse to a Moderator</u></a>
				
		</td>
			
		</tr>
	</table>
	
		











	







