		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>I think lawyers have outsmarted the jury system, I'm kinda in favor of judicial tribunals where three educated judges make decisions... the whole concept of jury by your peers worked before studies of psychology and manipulation became the very root of some law practices.&nbsp; </P>
<P>We have a court system that is based around fact finding, and a jury of your peers would work in it... but it's also become too much about either side "winning"... with justice a far off ideal to explain the game they play.</P>
<P>Alas, I think we should have educated people making decisions who will not be as easily coerced by emotional/psychological jury tampering which is a well perfected art these days.&nbsp; Its a shame that lawyers have corrupted one of the great ideas behind our lower court system... but they study 8 years and get many years of experience with the sole purpose of manipulating people who don't have the kind of training and understanding that they do.&nbsp; Most bad judicial decisions are not based on bad cases, but failures due to a flawed system.</P>
<P>So many cases are a parade, a circus, not a quest for justice and truth... really dissapointing.</P>
<DIV></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
