		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>Thought I should do an update.</P>
<P>I did report for my jury duty last week and spent my required service as two pleasant days in the "big room" doing puzzles with some other ladies.&nbsp; This was my first time at the Kent Regional Center instead of Downtown Seattle and the facilities were quite nice.</P>
<P>I did get selected for the pool (juror 48 out of 50) for what looked like a pretty nasty trial judging by the questionnaire we were given.&nbsp; However, that trial was motioned and delayed and postponed for another day, so we didn't even go out for the selection process.</P>
<P>For the person who asked about lost wages, many (but not all) employers will pay you your regular salary while on jury duty.&nbsp;&nbsp; Some require that you then give them your juror pay.&nbsp; So I do get a total of $20 plus a small mileage allowance for my two days.</P>
<P>In not-so-good news, on my way into the courthouse on Thursday morning I tripped and fell full out and face down on the pavement.&nbsp; Scrapped my left hand and arm rather severely.&nbsp; Now on Monday I still have a minor amount of stiffness and booboos on my hand but I am recovering.&nbsp; Probably would be better for my hand if I didn't type/play EQ all weekend.</P>
<DIV></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
