		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>I only got taken in to the courtroom near the very end, and was in the group that they selected two alternates from. They had chosen the jury for the last case that needed one in the group before mine. </P>
<P>And you get $15 a day here, and $40 if you serve as a juror, plus mileage pay. My job will pay at least half a day's pay for jury duty, I believe, but there are some companies where you basically lose out on that day's pay. Hence, why it's such a hardship for some people.</P>
<DIV></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
